files.Title: Oqtane.Documentation.InternalApi_DoNotUse_MayChangeWithoutNotice
files.Summary: This attribute serves as metadata for other things to mark them as internal APIs. Use this on stuff you want to document publicly, but mark as internal so people are warned

files.Title: Oqtane.Documentation.PrivateApi
files.Summary: This attribute marks classes, methods, etc. as private APIs So they should not be publicly documented. By default, all APIs are private, so you only need this attribute on children of classes marked with [PublicApi].

files.Title: Oqtane.Documentation.PublicApi
files.Summary: This attribute marks classes, properties etc. as public APIs. Any API / code with this attribute will be published in the docs. You can apply it to anything, but usually you will only need it on classes.

files.Title: Oqtane.Documentation.WorkInProgressApi
files.Summary: This attribute marks APIs to be publicly documented with a clear warning that it's work in progress.
